d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.01218775-f78b-48c0-9889-a8b542668db6.prompt=IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service. d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.1f13cfb8-acc1-4f42-bf1e-df48e604b87e.description=Waits for the job to reach a specific state. If no state is specified, then this will wait for the job to reach an end state. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobID - The id of the job. status - The status to wait for the job to reach. If none is specified this will wait until the job is no longer running. timeout - The maximum number of milliseconds to wait for the job. If not specified, 1 hour is used. Responses\: failure - Something went wrong. success - The operation completed successfully. d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.2622da6c-37ec-4cfe-9931-ebaa7e79f60c.prompt=Username of the SA. d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.29b6fd61-118c-4733-a0fe-f239bde3939e.prompt=Enter a value for jobID d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.61ffb1e8-9467-486a-8360-57054c1e180a.prompt=Enter a value for corePassword d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.6b7ae0a5-8d9a-45e5-9639-5ffea6794922.prompt=Enter a value for coreHost d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.96812c30-2035-4e3f-b1f8-70132ff1aad4.prompt=Enter a value for coreHost d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.b96e60c3-a510-48c4-bf0d-69211977b4a8.prompt=Password of SA user. d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.bed48629-30e4-4091-b557-ac00264e1951.prompt=Enter a value for coreUsername d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.c367e10e-a0b9-4956-b26e-401c6525c6f2.prompt=Enter a value for coreHost d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.cfcc1856-7c09-4f3c-bdf3-bade12ae176b.prompt=Enter a value for jobID d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.description=
Waits for an SA job to complete.

Inputs\:
coreHost		- The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core.
corePort		- The port to connect to your SAS core on.
coreProtocol		- The protocol to connect to your SAS core with, using either HTTP or HTTPS.
coreUsername	- The username for host.
corePassword	- The password for host.
coreVersion		- The version of SAS to use.
jobID		- The job ID of the task.
timeout		- The timeout value for the wait operation. It defaults to 20 minutes.
counter		- The number of time in millseconds that the flow should wait. It defaults to 1 hour.

Responses\:
success		- The flow waited successfully till the job completed.
failure		- The flow failed while waiting for the job to complete.
d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.e4c0f3e8-3aff-47ae-adc1-d1d152c0a748.prompt=Enter a value for coreUsername d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.e7157581-f7ee-4d56-88ab-4f8156431887.description=
This operation can be used to find the SA version in the form of 'sasXXX' (Similar to the entries in the Selection List 'SAS Version'). Output of this operations  could be mapped to the input parameter 'coreVersion' which is used in other SA Operations. For SA version 6.x, this operation is not supported. For other SA versions, if the output variable 'coreVersion' is reported with 'UNKNOWN', then user is recommended to manually find the SA version to use in other SA Operations.

Inputs\:
coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service.
corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443'.
coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS'.
coreUsername - Username of the SA.
corePassword - Password of SA user.

Outputs\:
status - Operation completion Status.
coreVersion - SA version.  It could be one of [sas7, sas75, sas78, sas9, sas91, UNKNOWN].

Responses\:
success - retrieved successfully
failure - failed to retrieve data
d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.e8b17776-f49c-4c55-86e6-870653efd788.description=Retrieves the properties for a Job Info. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobID - the id of the job Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data Returns\: description - The description of this object. blockedReason - The reason why this job is blocked. cancelledReason - The reason why this job is canceled. endDate - The date at which this job will cease to run. notificationFailureOwner - The user who will own this job if it fails. notificationSuccessOwner - The user who will own this job if it completes. notificationFailureRecipients - A ; delimited list of users who will receive notification if this job fails. notificationSuccessRecipients - A ; delimited list of users who will receive notification if this job completes. serverName - The name of the server associated with this job. serverId - The id of the server associated with this job. staleDate - The date after which this job is considered stale. startDate - The date where this job started. status - This object's status. username - This object's user name. userTag - This object's unique user tag. d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.ed422d89-3a5f-478f-8532-614b6f418870.description=Checks to see if a job is completed or not Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobID - the id of the job Responses\: running - job is still running completed - job has completed or is terminated in error failure - failed to retrieve data d518e662-c2bb-4a96-8023-00ee2fb1a034.f1c71e4b-45bd-42d3-a0e8-937b81889326.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
